{"questionId":"22170","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.&nbsp;The following diagram shows part&nbsp;of the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/29f29eec5cecfedc2512cc4dd4ed4d03516a589e.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>find the coordinates of the vertex.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to complete the square&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mfenced><mr